1
00:00:30,218 --> 00:00:33,221
[ominous music playing]

2
00:00:51,281 --> 00:00:54,284
[music intensifies]

3
00:01:19,434 --> 00:01:21,436
[townspeople speaking in Italian]

4
00:01:31,446 --> 00:01:34,449
[Amorth in Italian]
That's a beautiful pig.

5
00:01:34,532 --> 00:01:38,161
[in Italian]
Only the best, Father.

6
00:01:39,537 --> 00:01:41,205
[in Italian]
This way, Father.

7
00:02:01,601 --> 00:02:03,478
[in Italian] The boy is showing

8
00:02:03,561 --> 00:02:06,689
all the classical signs of possession,
Father Amorth.

9
00:02:07,648 --> 00:02:09,776
Has the family consulted a doctor?

10
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:12,987
Many, many doctors.

11
00:02:14,113 --> 00:02:17,158
What are the signs of possession?

12
00:02:17,742 --> 00:02:19,160
He converses in English, Father.

13
00:02:19,243 --> 00:02:20,787
- [boy yells]
- [thuds]

14
00:02:20,870 --> 00:02:23,247
Has he spoken English before?

15
00:02:23,331 --> 00:02:25,208
Never. Not once before.

16
00:02:26,125 --> 00:02:28,211
Do they own a television?

17
00:02:28,961 --> 00:02:30,171
Yes, I believe so.

18
00:02:31,964 --> 00:02:33,508
Okay, thank you.

19
00:02:33,591 --> 00:02:35,593
[boy yelling and groaning]

20
00:02:39,972 --> 00:02:41,224
[Amorth] Ah...

21
00:02:41,307 --> 00:02:43,351
What are you drawing?

22
00:02:43,434 --> 00:02:44,644
A bird.

23
00:02:46,687 --> 00:02:50,566
That's good, kid.

24
00:02:50,650 --> 00:02:52,443
[yelling continues]

25
00:02:52,527 --> 00:02:55,738
I have a very important job for you.

26
00:02:59,158 --> 00:03:00,576
Do you know the Our Father?

27
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:03,621
- Yes, Father.
- Good.

28
00:03:04,414 --> 00:03:05,623
[thuds continue]

29
00:03:06,874 --> 00:03:09,669
You can help your brother.

30
00:03:09,752 --> 00:03:15,842
Repeat the Our Father, over and over.

31
00:03:16,426 --> 00:03:21,431
Don't get distracted.
Relentless. Understood?

32
00:03:23,307 --> 00:03:24,684
Yes, Father.

33
00:03:25,518 --> 00:03:26,352
Good.

34
00:03:28,104 --> 00:03:34,444
Our Father, who art in heaven,
hallowed be thy name...

35
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,867
Bring me the pig.

36
00:03:40,950 --> 00:03:43,953
- [ominous music playing]
- [screaming continues]

37
00:03:45,955 --> 00:03:47,957
[gasping and grunting]

38
00:04:03,890 --> 00:04:06,350
[in English] I am legion.

39
00:04:08,728 --> 00:04:10,521
I am Satan.

40
00:04:13,274 --> 00:04:17,111
I am foul-mouthed behemoth.

41
00:04:18,738 --> 00:04:20,656
[in Italian] Difficult to believe.

42
00:04:23,701 --> 00:04:24,911
You doubt me?

43
00:04:24,994 --> 00:04:28,706
If you are Satan, what is my name?

44
00:04:31,459 --> 00:04:33,169
Describe hell.

45
00:04:35,671 --> 00:04:39,133
You will find out soon enough.

46
00:04:39,675 --> 00:04:41,969
Are you avoiding my questions?

47
00:04:42,053 --> 00:04:43,179
You mock me?

48
00:04:44,639 --> 00:04:47,642
[dramatic music playing]

49
00:04:50,603 --> 00:04:52,980
Answer me, Satan.

50
00:04:55,858 --> 00:04:58,945
Why possess this boy?

51
00:04:59,028 --> 00:05:01,572
Why not someone more influential?

52
00:05:01,656 --> 00:05:06,452
I can possess anyone I choose.

53
00:05:06,869 --> 00:05:07,703
Ah.

54
00:05:08,829 --> 00:05:11,415
Could you possess Father Gianni?

55
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:13,626
A bishop?

56
00:05:13,709 --> 00:05:16,504
- Anyone! Anything!
- [speaks in Italian]

57
00:05:16,587 --> 00:05:18,089
[in English] I do not believe you.

58
00:05:18,172 --> 00:05:21,592
I don't believe
you could even possess this pig.

59
00:05:22,343 --> 00:05:24,720
Can you do it? You have the power.

60
00:05:24,804 --> 00:05:26,556
Could you possess the pig?

61
00:05:26,639 --> 00:05:28,266
- Yes, I can.
- Come on, Satan.

62
00:05:28,349 --> 00:05:29,183
[boy] Watch me!

63
00:05:29,267 --> 00:05:32,228
[Amorth] Possess the pig.
Show me you are the Prince of Darkness.

64
00:05:32,311 --> 00:05:33,896
[speaks in Italian]

65
00:05:33,980 --> 00:05:35,356
[in English] Show to me your power.

66
00:05:35,439 --> 00:05:36,440
Have you done it?

67
00:05:36,524 --> 00:05:38,401
[in Italian]
Have you possessed him, Satan?

68
00:05:38,484 --> 00:05:39,318
[squeals]

69
00:05:40,319 --> 00:05:42,238
Have you possessed it, Satan?

70
00:05:45,199 --> 00:05:46,158
[pig screeches]

71
00:05:48,661 --> 00:05:50,079
[gasping and whimpering]

72
00:05:53,499 --> 00:05:54,667
Be calm.

73
00:05:56,002 --> 00:05:58,963
God blesses you.

74
00:05:59,046 --> 00:06:00,715
[in English] You can sleep now, my son.

75
00:06:00,798 --> 00:06:02,633
The demon has gone.

76
00:06:08,848 --> 00:06:10,308
<i>God is with you.</i>

77
00:06:11,309 --> 00:06:14,312
[haunting music playing]

78
00:06:21,402 --> 00:06:24,405
["She Sells Sanctuary" playing]

79
00:06:38,210 --> 00:06:40,504
<i>♪ Oh, the heads that turn ♪</i>

80
00:06:41,714 --> 00:06:43,883
<i>♪ Make my back burn ♪</i>

81
00:06:44,759 --> 00:06:47,345
<i>♪ And those heads that turn ♪</i>

82
00:06:48,471 --> 00:06:52,516
<i>♪ Make my back, make my back burn... ♪</i>

83
00:06:55,686 --> 00:06:58,189
[song continues over headphones]

84
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:09,575
Amy, we're not in America anymore.
You can't dress like that.

85
00:07:11,077 --> 00:07:11,911
Why?

86
00:07:11,994 --> 00:07:14,622
Because there's gonna be
construction workers everywhere.

87
00:07:15,164 --> 00:07:16,248
[scoffs]

88
00:07:17,667 --> 00:07:19,001
How you doing back there?

89
00:07:19,710 --> 00:07:23,673
<i>♪ The world and the world... ♪</i>

90
00:07:23,756 --> 00:07:26,759
[ominous music playing]

91
00:07:46,946 --> 00:07:49,198
[construction workers
chattering indistinctly]

92
00:07:50,574 --> 00:07:53,244
So we left everything for this?

93
00:07:53,327 --> 00:07:55,246
Amy, please. Don't start.

94
00:07:55,329 --> 00:07:59,208
- You know exactly what I'm gonna say.
- Yes, and I don't wanna hear it.

95
00:08:01,001 --> 00:08:03,003
What do you think? Pretty cool, huh?

96
00:08:05,631 --> 00:08:06,924
Yeah, I know.

97
00:08:07,883 --> 00:08:10,886
- [soft chattering in Italian]
- [church bells ringing]

98
00:08:16,851 --> 00:08:17,727
Cuckoo!

99
00:08:17,810 --> 00:08:18,894
[laughing]

100
00:08:18,978 --> 00:08:20,438
- [mimics roar]
- [giggling]

101
00:08:25,276 --> 00:08:27,528
Ah... Gabriele.

102
00:08:29,905 --> 00:08:32,783
[in Italian]
Why do you think Saint Michael

103
00:08:32,867 --> 00:08:35,536
didn't kill Satan when he had the chance?

104
00:08:36,203 --> 00:08:38,914
[in English]
That is a question of theology.

105
00:08:41,167 --> 00:08:42,376
[in English] No shit.

106
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:46,756
Perhaps it was his mercy
that stayed Saint Michael's sword.

107
00:08:46,839 --> 00:08:49,425
The only thing that arrests God's love

108
00:08:50,176 --> 00:08:52,470
is a person's freedom to choose.

109
00:08:53,095 --> 00:08:58,017
But God cannot be God
unless he allows for this choice

110
00:08:58,100 --> 00:08:59,727
even for the damned.

111
00:09:00,311 --> 00:09:01,854
Saint Michael, he knows this.

112
00:09:03,314 --> 00:09:06,150
We will all be judged.

113
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:07,651
We will all be judged

114
00:09:08,444 --> 00:09:10,237
by how much we love.

115
00:09:10,321 --> 00:09:11,447
[Lumumba] Hm.

116
00:09:11,530 --> 00:09:13,491
Do not worry, Gabriele.

117
00:09:14,283 --> 00:09:16,911
I will defend you.

118
00:09:16,994 --> 00:09:18,162
Defend me?

119
00:09:18,245 --> 00:09:19,497
Mm.

120
00:09:21,373 --> 00:09:22,500
My faith

121
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:25,002
does not require defense.

122
00:09:27,963 --> 00:09:29,423
[hammering]

123
00:09:29,507 --> 00:09:30,966
[indistinct chatter]

124
00:09:31,050 --> 00:09:31,967
[Julia] Oh-ho!

125
00:09:33,052 --> 00:09:34,178
Wow.

126
00:09:34,261 --> 00:09:37,097
- What do you think, guys?
- Cozy.

127
00:09:37,181 --> 00:09:40,559
[Julia] Oh, come on.
Give it a chance. This is awesome.

128
00:09:41,477 --> 00:09:44,021
- Señora Vasquez.
- Carlos, hi!

129
00:09:44,104 --> 00:09:45,815
So nice to put a face to the voice.

130
00:09:46,524 --> 00:09:47,358
Um...

131
00:09:47,817 --> 00:09:50,236
<i>Padre--</i> Father Esquibel...

132
00:09:50,319 --> 00:09:52,947
- Pleasure to meet you, Miss Vasquez.
- Uh, Julia, please.

133
00:09:53,030 --> 00:09:55,616
- Carlos was giving me a tour.
- [Julia] Oh, great.

134
00:09:55,699 --> 00:09:59,119
I just wanted to stop by and welcome
you and your family to the diocese.

135
00:09:59,203 --> 00:10:01,497
- [Carlos] I'm sorry.
- Oh, no, no, no, please. Go for it.

136
00:10:01,580 --> 00:10:03,374
I'm glad to see you made it safe.

137
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:05,835
[Amy] All right. Go find your room, twerp.

138
00:10:05,918 --> 00:10:10,130
- [saw buzzing, then metal clanks]
- [construction workers chattering]

139
00:10:11,924 --> 00:10:14,009
Hey. Can I get one of those?

140
00:10:14,093 --> 00:10:15,261
[in Italian] Yes, of course.

141
00:10:15,344 --> 00:10:17,596
[Esquibel]
This property has been in disrepair

142
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:19,473
- for as long as I can remember.
- Thank you.

143
00:10:19,557 --> 00:10:23,227
So it's a wonderful thing you're doing,
restoring the abbey.

144
00:10:23,310 --> 00:10:25,980
We are being very respectful
of the existing architecture.

145
00:10:26,063 --> 00:10:28,941
This has actually been
in my husband's family for generations,

146
00:10:29,024 --> 00:10:30,568
and we just inherited it.

147
00:10:30,651 --> 00:10:32,653
Is Mr. Vasquez here or--?

148
00:10:32,736 --> 00:10:36,407
Oh, uh, he passed, actually.
About a year ago.

149
00:10:36,490 --> 00:10:38,659
- I'm sorry for your loss.
- It's okay.

150
00:10:38,742 --> 00:10:42,413
If you need anything,
please, hm, don't hesitate.

151
00:10:42,496 --> 00:10:43,372
Okay.

152
00:10:43,956 --> 00:10:45,708
I will remember him in my prayers.

153
00:10:45,791 --> 00:10:48,586
Oh, that's very kind of you.
Thank you. It was nice to meet you.

154
00:10:49,086 --> 00:10:51,422
Okay, Carlos, talk to me.
What's up? Where are we at?

155
00:10:51,505 --> 00:10:53,632
The basement excavation
is very complicated.

156
00:10:53,716 --> 00:10:55,009
[Julia] More expensive, you mean?

157
00:10:55,092 --> 00:10:56,760
- [Carlos] I'm afraid so.
- [Julia] All right.

158
00:10:56,844 --> 00:10:58,262
I'll take another look at the plans.

159
00:10:58,345 --> 00:11:01,223
If you could just show me what the
basement looks like, maybe I can wire--

160
00:11:01,307 --> 00:11:04,435
Amy, get off of there
before you break your neck.

161
00:11:04,518 --> 00:11:07,438
Is that a cigarette?
Put that out right now, please.

162
00:11:07,521 --> 00:11:09,106
- Fine.
- No! Oh, my God.

163
00:11:11,984 --> 00:11:13,986
[plumbing groaning]

164
00:11:17,907 --> 00:11:19,658
[rhythmic knocking]

165
00:11:19,742 --> 00:11:22,745
[ominous music playing]

166
00:11:37,468 --> 00:11:39,261
[rhythmic knocking]

167
00:11:44,308 --> 00:11:45,809
[music fades]

168
00:11:45,893 --> 00:11:46,810
Cute.

169
00:11:47,311 --> 00:11:48,520
Get out of my room.

170
00:11:52,858 --> 00:11:54,902
[rhythmic knocking]

171
00:11:58,197 --> 00:12:01,200
["Gone Daddy Gone"
playing over headphones]

172
00:12:04,036 --> 00:12:06,830
<i>♪ Beautiful girl, lovely dress ♪</i>

173
00:12:06,914 --> 00:12:09,500
<i>♪ Where she is now, I can only guess ♪</i>

174
00:12:09,583 --> 00:12:12,461
<i>♪ 'Cause it's gone, daddy, gone
The love is gone ♪</i>

175
00:12:12,544 --> 00:12:15,381
<i>♪ Yeah, it's gone, daddy, gone
The love is gone ♪</i>

176
00:12:15,464 --> 00:12:17,466
<i>♪ Yeah, it's gone, daddy, gone... ♪</i>

177
00:12:17,549 --> 00:12:20,552
[haunting music playing]

178
00:12:21,387 --> 00:12:23,389
[man speaking in Spanish]

179
00:12:43,951 --> 00:12:48,455
[thumping]

180
00:12:48,539 --> 00:12:49,957
- [masonry clatters]
- [gasps]

181
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:53,752
[indistinct demonic whispers]

182
00:13:08,684 --> 00:13:11,895
[stones crackling and crunching]

183
00:13:14,648 --> 00:13:17,651
["We Care A Lot" playing over headphones]

184
00:13:19,862 --> 00:13:20,696
[knocking on door]

185
00:13:21,447 --> 00:13:23,115
Hey, have you seen your brother?

186
00:13:24,783 --> 00:13:25,617
Amy.

187
00:13:30,831 --> 00:13:36,128
Look, I really can't handle
the silent treatment from both my kids.

188
00:13:37,588 --> 00:13:40,215
- I know you don't wanna be here.
- Yeah, no shit.

189
00:13:40,299 --> 00:13:41,133
Amy.

190
00:13:42,092 --> 00:13:44,720
Please, I need your help.

191
00:13:44,803 --> 00:13:46,847
This abbey is the only thing
your dad left us.

192
00:13:46,930 --> 00:13:48,474
We don't have an income anymore.

193
00:13:48,557 --> 00:13:51,894
Once we fix it up and sell it,
we'll go home. Okay?

194
00:13:53,020 --> 00:13:55,647
Maybe if you could just
at least watch your brother.

195
00:13:55,731 --> 00:13:57,232
Maybe try and get him to talk.

196
00:13:57,316 --> 00:13:59,860
How? He hasn't spoken in almost a year.

197
00:14:00,569 --> 00:14:02,321
Can you try for me?

198
00:14:02,404 --> 00:14:04,323
So you want me to be a mother for you?

199
00:14:04,406 --> 00:14:07,284
Please just keep an eye
on your brother. Okay?

200
00:14:08,285 --> 00:14:09,369
[mouths]

201
00:14:10,662 --> 00:14:13,665
["We Care A Lot" continues]

202
00:14:14,666 --> 00:14:16,752
<i>♪ Whoa, whoa ♪</i>

203
00:14:16,835 --> 00:14:20,547
<i>♪ It's a dirty job
But someone's gotta do it ♪</i>

204
00:14:25,719 --> 00:14:28,889
<i>♪ It's a dirty job
But someone's gotta do it ♪</i>

205
00:14:28,972 --> 00:14:30,140
<i>♪ We care a lot ♪</i>

206
00:14:30,224 --> 00:14:31,225
[song ends]

207
00:14:32,226 --> 00:14:33,143
[in Italian] Hold this.

208
00:14:33,227 --> 00:14:35,229
[church bells ringing]

209
00:14:40,651 --> 00:14:43,946
Father Amorth, caffe latte?

210
00:14:44,029 --> 00:14:47,324
At this time of the day? Are you crazy?

211
00:14:49,243 --> 00:14:51,578
Double espresso, Sister.

212
00:14:51,662 --> 00:14:52,830
Thank you.

213
00:14:52,913 --> 00:14:54,123
[in English] Sugar?

214
00:14:54,206 --> 00:14:57,543
Sugar is the work of the devil.
No, thank you.

215
00:15:01,922 --> 00:15:02,965
Thank you very much.

216
00:15:05,968 --> 00:15:08,470
Let's get on with this already.

217
00:15:09,847 --> 00:15:11,807
[in English] This is a formal hearing.

218
00:15:11,890 --> 00:15:15,060
And as agreed,
proceedings will be undertaken in English.

219
00:15:15,144 --> 00:15:17,938
Ah. All right, let's go.

220
00:15:18,021 --> 00:15:20,858
On the night of June 4th,
in the town of Tropea,

221
00:15:21,441 --> 00:15:23,193
you performed an exorcism

222
00:15:23,277 --> 00:15:26,738
without the approval
of the Reggio Calabria bishop.

223
00:15:27,364 --> 00:15:28,699
It wasn't a--

224
00:15:28,782 --> 00:15:30,325
In English, Father Amorth.

225
00:15:32,452 --> 00:15:35,205
[in English] That was not an exorcism.

226
00:15:35,289 --> 00:15:38,959
From Father Gianni's description,
what occurred in Reggio Calabria sounded

227
00:15:39,042 --> 00:15:42,963
exactly like an exorcism,
complete with animal sacrifice, no less.

228
00:15:43,046 --> 00:15:46,091
The boy was maladjusted.
A temporary mental illness.

229
00:15:46,175 --> 00:15:48,886
I use primitive psychology.

230
00:15:49,553 --> 00:15:51,138
The power of suggestion.

231
00:15:51,221 --> 00:15:55,601
You addressed the subject as Satan,
called for him to display his power.

232
00:15:56,560 --> 00:15:58,312
- Do you deny this?
- No.

233
00:15:59,146 --> 00:16:01,690
- That's what I did.
- And why would you do that?

234
00:16:01,773 --> 00:16:03,483
Exorcism is my job,

235
00:16:04,026 --> 00:16:07,112
but the vast majority of the cases
to which I'm assigned

236
00:16:07,196 --> 00:16:09,948
do not require an exorcism.

237
00:16:10,657 --> 00:16:13,410
They just need, uh, a little conversation,

238
00:16:14,203 --> 00:16:16,038
a little understanding,

239
00:16:16,121 --> 00:16:17,539
and sometimes...

240
00:16:18,749 --> 00:16:19,958
a little theater.

241
00:16:20,542 --> 00:16:23,587
Cardinal Sullivan, in my observation,

242
00:16:24,129 --> 00:16:27,341
98% of the cases
that are assigned to Father Amorth

243
00:16:27,424 --> 00:16:30,344
are then further recommended by him

244
00:16:30,427 --> 00:16:32,804
to doctors and psychiatrists.

245
00:16:32,888 --> 00:16:34,348
And the other 2%?

246
00:16:35,182 --> 00:16:36,975
[Amorth] Ah, the other 2%.

247
00:16:37,684 --> 00:16:40,729
This is something
that has confounded all of science

248
00:16:40,812 --> 00:16:43,023
and all of medicine for a very long time.

249
00:16:43,106 --> 00:16:46,026
[ominous music playing]

250
00:16:46,109 --> 00:16:47,402
I call it...

251
00:16:48,737 --> 00:16:49,571
evil.

252
00:16:49,655 --> 00:16:52,991
[Lumumba] Your Eminence,
with hundreds of successful exorcisms,

253
00:16:53,075 --> 00:16:57,579
- Father Amorth has been very effective--
- One moment, Bishop Lumumba.

254
00:16:58,997 --> 00:17:01,333
You do raise an interesting point, Amorth.

255
00:17:01,917 --> 00:17:05,003
You are not a doctor,
but these practices of yours

256
00:17:05,087 --> 00:17:07,130
could have damaging effects
on these people.

257
00:17:07,798 --> 00:17:08,799
You are right.

258
00:17:09,591 --> 00:17:10,968
I am not a doctor.

259
00:17:11,927 --> 00:17:13,887
I am not a psychologist.

260
00:17:15,347 --> 00:17:17,557
But I am a theologian, I am a lawyer,

261
00:17:17,641 --> 00:17:20,477
I am a journalist,
and I am a practical man.

262
00:17:20,978 --> 00:17:25,649
I was also a partisan in the war,
so I know a firing squad when I see one.

263
00:17:28,860 --> 00:17:30,404
So, what is this about?

264
00:17:30,487 --> 00:17:32,823
The Congregation
for the Doctrine of the Faith

265
00:17:32,906 --> 00:17:34,491
has recommended to this panel

266
00:17:34,992 --> 00:17:39,913
that the position of chief exorcist
be formally vacated.

267
00:17:39,997 --> 00:17:42,791
So, what you are saying
is that evil does not exist?

268
00:17:42,874 --> 00:17:45,794
The Church is under constant pressure
to sharpen her relevance.

269
00:17:45,877 --> 00:17:48,672
It's time we move past
these outdated beliefs.

270
00:17:48,755 --> 00:17:51,091
Explain to me please, Your Eminence.

271
00:17:51,591 --> 00:17:53,093
If evil does not exist,

272
00:17:53,677 --> 00:17:57,139
what, then, is the role of the Church?

273
00:17:58,765 --> 00:18:03,020
I think we all have to be careful of the
Congregation of the Doctrine of the Faith.

274
00:18:03,562 --> 00:18:06,356
Sounds to me
like they want us all out of a job.

275
00:18:11,945 --> 00:18:14,406
We have more questions for you,
Father Amorth.

276
00:18:18,076 --> 00:18:20,620
How is it that I am suddenly worthy

277
00:18:20,704 --> 00:18:23,332
of the time and attention
of all you powerful men?

278
00:18:24,041 --> 00:18:25,250
I ask you again...

279
00:18:26,543 --> 00:18:27,878
what is this about?

280
00:18:27,961 --> 00:18:29,296
Due process, Father.

281
00:18:29,379 --> 00:18:32,716
So this is not about the dead girl,
Rosaria Velendez,

282
00:18:32,799 --> 00:18:35,635
<i>that I write about
in</i> La Madre di Dio <i>magazine?</i>

283
00:18:35,719 --> 00:18:37,971
What is your due diligence
and process on this?

284
00:18:38,055 --> 00:18:41,058
- Please, cardinal.
- I warn you! I warn you! Father Amorth,

285
00:18:41,141 --> 00:18:42,851
show respect to your superiors.

286
00:18:42,934 --> 00:18:44,311
I do!

287
00:18:44,394 --> 00:18:46,813
I am the chief exorcist of the Vatican.

288
00:18:46,897 --> 00:18:49,816
My position was appointed by my bishop.

289
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:51,693
My diocese is Rome.

290
00:18:51,777 --> 00:18:53,528
My local bishop is the pope.

291
00:18:54,029 --> 00:18:55,739
If you have a problem with me,

292
00:18:56,448 --> 00:18:58,492
you talk to my boss. Okay?

293
00:18:59,368 --> 00:19:01,411
The pope is infirm.

294
00:19:01,495 --> 00:19:03,413
Father Amorth,
you have not been dismissed.

295
00:19:03,497 --> 00:19:04,998
- Cuckoo.
- Father Amorth!

296
00:19:05,582 --> 00:19:08,585
- [crickets chirping]
- [fire crackling]

297
00:19:25,310 --> 00:19:26,186
[sighs]

298
00:19:27,521 --> 00:19:29,523
[thudding]

299
00:19:33,235 --> 00:19:36,238
- [ominous music playing]
- [wind whistling]

300
00:19:37,697 --> 00:19:39,908
[clanking and thudding]

301
00:19:41,451 --> 00:19:42,494
[shivers]

302
00:19:44,079 --> 00:19:46,081
[clock ticking]

303
00:19:58,844 --> 00:19:59,678
Hello?

304
00:20:01,638 --> 00:20:02,681
Anyone there?

305
00:20:02,764 --> 00:20:04,266
- [floorboards creak]
- [gasps]

306
00:20:10,355 --> 00:20:13,358
[heavy metal music playing indistinctly
over headphones]

307
00:20:31,084 --> 00:20:33,086
[Walkman clicks, then music stops]

308
00:20:39,843 --> 00:20:42,846
[ominous music intensifies]

309
00:20:56,234 --> 00:20:58,653
[man in Spanish]
I can't wait to finish this job.

310
00:20:58,737 --> 00:21:00,030
This place freaks me out.

311
00:21:00,113 --> 00:21:02,115
[masonry crumbling]

312
00:21:06,203 --> 00:21:08,205
[indistinct demonic whispers]

313
00:21:09,539 --> 00:21:10,457
What is it?

314
00:21:13,043 --> 00:21:15,086
I don't know. Can't see anything.

315
00:21:29,476 --> 00:21:30,852
[yells]

316
00:21:32,979 --> 00:21:36,274
- [haunting music playing]
- [indistinct radio chatter]

317
00:21:38,693 --> 00:21:39,945
[Carlos] They hit a gas deposit.

318
00:21:40,529 --> 00:21:44,199
We can't continue working here.
I'm pulling my team from this place.

319
00:21:45,283 --> 00:21:47,369
[in Spanish]
Come on, let's go. Come on, everybody out.

320
00:21:47,452 --> 00:21:48,286
[Julia] Wait.

321
00:21:49,829 --> 00:21:50,997
[man] Quick, quick.

322
00:21:51,081 --> 00:21:54,084
[haunting music continues]

323
00:22:01,341 --> 00:22:02,676
[demonic snarl]

324
00:22:05,804 --> 00:22:06,638
[Amy] Henry?

325
00:22:07,264 --> 00:22:08,682
No. Henry!

326
00:22:09,975 --> 00:22:10,850
Mom!

327
00:22:12,310 --> 00:22:15,230
[Julia] Oh, my God!
Henry! What is happening?

328
00:22:15,313 --> 00:22:17,232
I don't know,
he was like this when I came in.

329
00:22:17,315 --> 00:22:19,651
Henry? Henry, it's Mommy.

330
00:22:19,734 --> 00:22:20,610
Talk to me.

331
00:22:21,778 --> 00:22:23,947
- Henry.
- Mommy.

332
00:22:24,030 --> 00:22:24,948
He's talking.

333
00:22:25,448 --> 00:22:27,951
- Henry.
- Mommy.

334
00:22:33,790 --> 00:22:35,792
You're all going to die.

335
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:38,336
[Julia] Henry! What are you doing?

336
00:22:38,420 --> 00:22:39,754
- Henry! Henry!
- [Amy] Henry! Henry!

337
00:22:39,838 --> 00:22:41,840
[MRI thumping]

338
00:22:51,182 --> 00:22:53,643
[woman]
<i>X-rays, blood tests, even the spinal tap</i>

339
00:22:53,727 --> 00:22:56,605
and MRI show no results
of ischemia or hematoma.

340
00:22:57,230 --> 00:22:58,481
What does that mean?

341
00:22:58,565 --> 00:23:01,359
[both speaking in Italian]

342
00:23:02,444 --> 00:23:06,698
[in English] All of his vitals
and brain functions seem to be normal.

343
00:23:06,781 --> 00:23:10,452
Wait, normal? What do you mean?
He was convulsing.

344
00:23:10,535 --> 00:23:12,537
[speaks in Italian]

345
00:23:12,621 --> 00:23:14,998
Has he been through any trauma recently?

346
00:23:18,043 --> 00:23:19,544
[sobs] Um...

347
00:23:20,629 --> 00:23:24,424
Yeah, uh, his dad died about a year ago.

348
00:23:25,258 --> 00:23:27,469
[both speak in Italian]

349
00:23:27,552 --> 00:23:29,095
[woman in English] And how did he react?

350
00:23:30,138 --> 00:23:31,139
Uh...

351
00:23:31,222 --> 00:23:32,766
He hasn't spoken since.

352
00:23:33,808 --> 00:23:35,894
[both speak in Italian]

353
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:39,147
Wha-- Psychosis?

354
00:23:39,230 --> 00:23:41,274
No, that's not possible.
He's just a little boy.

355
00:23:41,358 --> 00:23:45,111
[in English] Ma'am,
there is nothing that we can do now.

356
00:23:45,195 --> 00:23:48,615
- But he can recommend a good psychiatrist.
- [Julia] What is this?

357
00:23:48,698 --> 00:23:49,699
[speaks in Italian]

358
00:23:51,534 --> 00:23:54,204
If your son continues
trying to hurt himself,

359
00:23:54,287 --> 00:23:56,289
- you can administer him this sedative.
- No.

360
00:23:56,873 --> 00:23:58,166
- Mom.
- I'm so sorry.

361
00:23:58,833 --> 00:23:59,834
Baby.

362
00:23:59,918 --> 00:24:01,127
Oh, my God.

363
00:24:08,134 --> 00:24:10,220
[Julia] No, I don't think you understand.

364
00:24:10,887 --> 00:24:13,306
But this is an emergency, please.

365
00:24:13,390 --> 00:24:18,520
No, I need to talk to someone
at the consulate who can help me.

366
00:24:18,603 --> 00:24:20,230
I need a specialist.

367
00:24:21,815 --> 00:24:22,649
Okay.

368
00:24:24,234 --> 00:24:25,193
Okay.

369
00:24:25,985 --> 00:24:27,278
Yes, please.

370
00:24:28,446 --> 00:24:31,449
[ominous music playing]

371
00:24:43,503 --> 00:24:45,505
[bed creaks]

372
00:24:48,341 --> 00:24:49,634
[Julia] Baby.

373
00:24:53,471 --> 00:24:54,305
Hey.

374
00:24:55,515 --> 00:24:57,642
My love, come here.

375
00:25:04,566 --> 00:25:06,901
- [clattering]
- [mice squeaking]

376
00:25:12,115 --> 00:25:15,118
[electricity crackling and humming]

377
00:25:17,495 --> 00:25:18,413
Fuck this.

378
00:25:25,462 --> 00:25:27,130
- Henry, no.
- [growls]

379
00:25:27,213 --> 00:25:28,631
Henry, stop!

380
00:25:28,715 --> 00:25:30,508
This baby's hungry, you fat cow.

381
00:25:30,592 --> 00:25:32,427
What? What are you saying? [gasps]

382
00:25:32,510 --> 00:25:34,512
You never breastfed me, Mommy.

383
00:25:34,596 --> 00:25:35,722
- What?
- [Amy] What the fuck?

384
00:25:35,805 --> 00:25:37,932
- [Julia groans] Ow!
- [growls]

385
00:25:41,728 --> 00:25:43,229
What the fuck is that?

386
00:25:43,313 --> 00:25:45,899
Bring me the priest.

387
00:25:47,233 --> 00:25:49,110
- [Julia] Can you help us?
- [Esquibel] Yes.

388
00:25:50,069 --> 00:25:51,529
I'm here to help, Julia.

389
00:25:51,613 --> 00:25:52,447
Okay.

390
00:25:52,530 --> 00:25:55,533
[suspenseful music playing]

391
00:26:04,334 --> 00:26:05,794
- [Henry roars]
- [Esquibel grunts]

392
00:26:05,877 --> 00:26:06,836
[both scream]

393
00:26:08,004 --> 00:26:10,924
[in demonic voice] Wrong fucking priest!

394
00:26:11,007 --> 00:26:12,550
[roars]

395
00:26:27,565 --> 00:26:31,069
- [in Italian] Is that you, Gabriele?
- [in Italian] Yes, Holy Father.

396
00:26:32,070 --> 00:26:34,280
They tell me you are sick.

397
00:26:34,364 --> 00:26:36,616
Yes, they hope so.

398
00:26:37,492 --> 00:26:39,369
They wish to see me weak.

399
00:26:39,452 --> 00:26:41,454
But, no, they are.

400
00:26:42,497 --> 00:26:44,374
[sighs]

401
00:26:44,958 --> 00:26:46,626
- Help me.
- Yes.

402
00:27:07,689 --> 00:27:11,234
Perhaps we've done our jobs too well.

403
00:27:11,317 --> 00:27:13,945
Cardinal Sullivan
and the younger generation,

404
00:27:14,028 --> 00:27:17,073
they don't believe in the devil
as we understand it.

405
00:27:17,824 --> 00:27:23,788
It's only an idea for them.
For us, it is very real.

406
00:27:24,581 --> 00:27:26,499
Two hundred fallen angels,

407
00:27:26,583 --> 00:27:30,128
expelled from heaven, driven beneath
the soil where God is not welcomed.

408
00:27:31,254 --> 00:27:33,131
It is not a fairytale.

409
00:27:34,257 --> 00:27:38,094
Your search for truth
is delightful, Gabriele,

410
00:27:38,177 --> 00:27:42,015
but pay attention
to your desire to educate.

411
00:27:42,098 --> 00:27:46,436
Pride manifests itself in different forms.

412
00:27:48,062 --> 00:27:50,440
Pride? Me?

413
00:27:50,523 --> 00:27:51,649
[chuckles]

414
00:27:53,943 --> 00:27:56,362
[in English]
There's a case that needs your attention.

415
00:27:57,030 --> 00:27:58,448
A boy in Spain.

416
00:27:59,032 --> 00:28:03,286
Something about it disturbs me greatly.

417
00:28:04,078 --> 00:28:05,788
[pensive music playing]

418
00:28:05,872 --> 00:28:09,834
<i>This boy's possession
is progressing very fast.</i>

419
00:28:11,294 --> 00:28:14,589
<i>The incident took place
in hallowed ground,</i>

420
00:28:14,672 --> 00:28:17,425
<i>San Sebastian Abbey in Castile.</i>

421
00:28:19,886 --> 00:28:23,181
This place
has given the Church problems before.

422
00:28:24,265 --> 00:28:27,518
<i>I sense a great evil coming from there.</i>

423
00:28:28,061 --> 00:28:32,607
<i>Something dark
that only you can help solve.</i>

424
00:28:34,067 --> 00:28:37,904
<i>I have requested the abbey's records
be brought to you in the library.</i>

425
00:28:39,489 --> 00:28:40,448
<i>Look into it.</i>

426
00:28:41,866 --> 00:28:45,912
<i>I will continue investigating
while you're on your journey.</i>

427
00:28:50,875 --> 00:28:52,251
[in English] "Our sins...

428
00:28:53,670 --> 00:28:55,838
will seek us out."

429
00:28:57,090 --> 00:28:58,341
[Pope] <i>Gabriele.</i>

430
00:28:58,424 --> 00:29:01,886
Go to Spain, and help this child.

431
00:29:02,512 --> 00:29:06,557
But be careful,
this demon sounds dangerous.

432
00:29:07,225 --> 00:29:10,228
[ominous music playing]

433
00:30:03,239 --> 00:30:04,323
[Amorth] Hello?

434
00:30:04,407 --> 00:30:06,409
[music fades]

435
00:30:06,492 --> 00:30:08,494
[birds singing and insects chirping]

436
00:30:15,376 --> 00:30:17,670
[door creaks, then closes]

437
00:30:35,229 --> 00:30:36,272
[in Spanish] Father.

438
00:30:37,315 --> 00:30:40,526
Good morning.
I'm Father Tomás Esquibel.

439
00:30:41,652 --> 00:30:42,862
- [in Italian] Spanish?
- Yes.

440
00:30:43,738 --> 00:30:46,449
I am Father Amorth. Italian.

441
00:30:48,326 --> 00:30:51,496
- [in English] Wait. Father Amorth?
- Yes.

442
00:30:52,080 --> 00:30:55,083
Ah. I didn't expect them to send you.

443
00:30:55,166 --> 00:30:56,167
[in English] You know me?

444
00:30:56,250 --> 00:31:00,421
- Yes. I have read all the articles.
- [chuckles]

445
00:31:00,505 --> 00:31:03,382
- And the books?
- No, no. No, not the books.

446
00:31:04,801 --> 00:31:05,760
The books are good.

447
00:31:05,843 --> 00:31:08,763
- I will read--
- Okay. I'll just get my bag.

448
00:31:08,846 --> 00:31:11,057
You, uh... [clears throat] Whiskey?

449
00:31:11,933 --> 00:31:13,059
No, no, no. Thank you.

450
00:31:13,643 --> 00:31:16,771
[clears throat]
Yeah, this sore throat, the dust.

451
00:31:20,483 --> 00:31:23,861
Julia, we have been extremely lucky.
The Church sent someone.

452
00:31:23,945 --> 00:31:26,614
An expert in these matters.
Gabriele, please come in.

453
00:31:28,282 --> 00:31:31,119
[in Italian]
Good morning, good morning, good morning.

454
00:31:31,202 --> 00:31:32,161
I am Father Amorth.

455
00:31:32,954 --> 00:31:34,330
[in English] I have come from Roma.

456
00:31:34,413 --> 00:31:35,873
[in Italian] Gabriele, how are you?

457
00:31:37,208 --> 00:31:39,085
I'm sorry that you came all this way,

458
00:31:39,168 --> 00:31:41,838
but I don't even know
why the Church is interested in this.

459
00:31:41,921 --> 00:31:43,506
I just want my son to be well.

460
00:31:43,589 --> 00:31:44,423
[Amorth] Yes, yes.

461
00:31:44,507 --> 00:31:48,594
[in English] Tell me something,
have the doctors given you any answers?

462
00:31:49,095 --> 00:31:50,346
Any comfort?

463
00:31:51,013 --> 00:31:53,099
If you would at least...

464
00:31:54,308 --> 00:31:55,893
just let me see your son.

465
00:31:57,186 --> 00:32:00,314
I can give you my opinion
and you can do with it what you will.

466
00:32:05,653 --> 00:32:06,529
It's worth a shot.

467
00:32:10,158 --> 00:32:11,617
Okay. He's upstairs.

468
00:32:13,077 --> 00:32:15,663
[in Italian] Very nice, this.

469
00:32:17,707 --> 00:32:20,168
[in English] Hello, my friend. [chuckles]

470
00:32:38,186 --> 00:32:39,020
Henry.

471
00:32:40,104 --> 00:32:41,314
Are you awake?

472
00:32:43,816 --> 00:32:46,819
[ominous music playing]

473
00:33:39,163 --> 00:33:42,208
[in Italian]
Our Father, who art in heaven,

474
00:33:42,291 --> 00:33:46,379
hallowed be thy name.
Thy kingdom come, thy will be--

475
00:33:46,462 --> 00:33:49,382
[in English demonic voice]
Your prayers are worthless here.

476
00:33:58,516 --> 00:34:00,518
[growling]

477
00:34:23,624 --> 00:34:24,917
[in English] Who are you?

478
00:34:25,001 --> 00:34:29,672
Your worst fear. I am your demise.

479
00:34:30,798 --> 00:34:32,842
Why are you possessing this boy?

480
00:34:32,925 --> 00:34:37,763
Because it feels so good
to ruin such innocent flesh.

481
00:34:38,431 --> 00:34:42,226
But I prefer the challenge
of an exorcist's soul.

482
00:34:42,310 --> 00:34:44,603
You only serve to diminish yourself.

483
00:34:44,687 --> 00:34:47,023
Don't lecture me, priest.

484
00:34:47,106 --> 00:34:48,524
What is your purpose?

485
00:34:48,607 --> 00:34:50,568
I'm here for you.

486
00:34:52,486 --> 00:34:54,655
Then you must know my name.

487
00:34:55,281 --> 00:34:59,577
I know your soul and every shameless sin.

488
00:35:00,953 --> 00:35:03,080
Tell me one of my sins.

489
00:35:03,164 --> 00:35:04,790
[growls]

490
00:35:06,292 --> 00:35:07,418
You cannot.

491
00:35:08,878 --> 00:35:12,590
Because my sins have been absolved
by the one true master,

492
00:35:12,673 --> 00:35:14,675
- the Lord Jesus Christ.
- Do not speak of him.

493
00:35:14,759 --> 00:35:18,054
Are you afraid of him?
Are you afraid of Jesus Christ?

494
00:35:19,930 --> 00:35:22,308
[in Latin] God is not here.

495
00:35:23,017 --> 00:35:25,519
[in Latin] God is everywhere.

496
00:35:26,437 --> 00:35:27,730
[in English] Whatever you do...

497
00:35:28,898 --> 00:35:31,108
you only do because God allows it.

498
00:35:34,570 --> 00:35:35,988
Did he allow that?

499
00:35:36,906 --> 00:35:38,699
This is just the beginning.

500
00:35:38,783 --> 00:35:40,743
You don't know who you're dealing with.

501
00:35:41,911 --> 00:35:44,663
Then tell me. Tell me your name.

502
00:35:45,247 --> 00:35:46,749
Unless you are too afraid.

503
00:35:46,832 --> 00:35:51,128
I'm not some stupid fuck
you convince to get into a pig.

504
00:35:51,712 --> 00:35:53,798
So you won't tell me your name.

505
00:35:54,423 --> 00:35:57,259
My name is blasphemy.

506
00:35:58,010 --> 00:36:01,972
My name is nightmare.

507
00:36:03,224 --> 00:36:04,058
Ah.

508
00:36:07,978 --> 00:36:09,313
My nightmare...

509
00:36:10,481 --> 00:36:13,275
is France winning the World Cup.

510
00:36:13,359 --> 00:36:15,319
You prideful fool.

511
00:36:15,403 --> 00:36:18,280
You can't hide
behind your jokes forever...

512
00:36:19,698 --> 00:36:21,659
Gabriele.

513
00:36:22,952 --> 00:36:25,121
I know your nightmares too.

514
00:36:26,372 --> 00:36:28,457
