See thee beneath God!

1293
01:31:44,895 --> 01:31:47,148
Tomás! Pray the final rites.

1294
01:31:48,607 --> 01:31:54,321
In the name of the Father,
and of the Son, and of the Holy Spirit...

1295
01:31:55,322 --> 01:31:57,241
see thee beneath God!

1296
01:31:57,324 --> 01:31:59,118
[roars]

1297
01:32:15,342 --> 01:32:17,845
[coughs, then groans]

1298
01:32:18,971 --> 01:32:21,557
Gabriele, are you okay?

1299
01:32:27,438 --> 01:32:28,481
Not so bad.

1300
01:32:29,273 --> 01:32:31,275
[coughing]

1301
01:32:33,319 --> 01:32:35,029
- Tomás.
- What?

1302
01:32:36,572 --> 01:32:37,990
You look like shit.

1303
01:32:38,073 --> 01:32:39,074
[Amorth chuckles]

1304
01:32:41,994 --> 01:32:43,496
Bless you, Tomás.

1305
01:32:44,455 --> 01:32:46,081
You learned the Latin.

1306
01:32:46,165 --> 01:32:47,166
[laughs]

1307
01:32:47,958 --> 01:32:50,669
Yes, it's similar to the Spanish.

1308
01:32:50,753 --> 01:32:53,422
[laughs] Very similar to the Spanish.

1309
01:32:57,510 --> 01:32:58,594
Look.

1310
01:33:03,098 --> 01:33:08,395
You know, the God,
he works in very mysterious ways.

1311
01:33:14,235 --> 01:33:15,069
For you.

1312
01:33:15,152 --> 01:33:18,155
[hopeful music playing]

1313
01:33:23,661 --> 01:33:26,330
Yes, he does.

1314
01:33:28,749 --> 01:33:31,752
[hopeful music continues]

1315
01:33:35,172 --> 01:33:36,006
Cuckoo.

1316
01:33:44,765 --> 01:33:46,267
Is that you, Gabriele?

1317
01:33:46,851 --> 01:33:48,811
[Amorth in Italian] Yes, Your Holiness.

1318
01:33:48,894 --> 01:33:51,605
[in English] And I have brought
Padre Esquibel to meet you.

1319
01:33:51,689 --> 01:33:53,566
You look well, Your Holiness.

1320
01:33:53,649 --> 01:33:56,235
Thanks to you both. I'm glad to see you.

1321
01:33:57,027 --> 01:33:58,821
You had me worried this time.

1322
01:33:59,488 --> 01:34:01,031
Sounded dangerous.

1323
01:34:01,115 --> 01:34:02,908
[in Italian] Yeah, not too bad.

1324
01:34:03,951 --> 01:34:06,579
Sometimes you fly
a little too close to the sun.

1325
01:34:07,663 --> 01:34:09,248
[in English] It has not killed me yet.

1326
01:34:09,331 --> 01:34:11,542
The Church will not forget
what you have done.

1327
01:34:11,625 --> 01:34:15,421
You struck a mighty blow for our side.

1328
01:34:15,504 --> 01:34:18,132
Saint Michael would be proud.

1329
01:34:19,091 --> 01:34:22,303
And this is why God
put you here, Gabriele.

1330
01:34:22,386 --> 01:34:24,388
[in Italian]
Thank you very much, Your Holiness.

1331
01:34:24,471 --> 01:34:29,018
And God has made a good choice
in you too, Father Esquibel.

1332
01:34:29,101 --> 01:34:30,436
Thank you, Holy Father.

1333
01:34:30,519 --> 01:34:35,900
The congregation
has requested a full report on Spain.

1334
01:34:35,983 --> 01:34:37,359
[in English] A full report.

1335
01:34:37,443 --> 01:34:42,197
So Cardinal Sullivan can tell me again
that evil only exists in my imagination?

1336
01:34:42,281 --> 01:34:43,198
You haven't heard?

1337
01:34:43,866 --> 01:34:47,870
Cardinal Sullivan has taken a sabbatical
in the Isle of Guam.

1338
01:34:51,165 --> 01:34:54,084
I shall pray for Guam.

1339
01:34:56,503 --> 01:34:59,924
And who has, uh, filled his shoes?

1340
01:35:00,007 --> 01:35:03,844
I have found someone far more trustworthy.

1341
01:35:05,137 --> 01:35:07,598
I will leave you in his good hands.

1342
01:35:12,144 --> 01:35:15,147
See thee beneath God.

1343
01:35:15,230 --> 01:35:17,107
- See thee beneath God.
- See thee beneath God.

1344
01:35:18,776 --> 01:35:20,819
[church bells ringing]

1345
01:35:22,029 --> 01:35:24,740
[Lumumba]
Welcome to the holiest of holies.

1346
01:35:24,823 --> 01:35:26,533
Twelve centuries of treasures.

1347
01:35:27,117 --> 01:35:29,620
Letters from saints and apostles.

1348
01:35:29,703 --> 01:35:32,373
Books of wisdom and piety.

1349
01:35:32,456 --> 01:35:34,291
Revelations of the spirit.

1350
01:35:34,875 --> 01:35:38,420
The entire canon of Christian thought.

1351
01:35:39,588 --> 01:35:42,216
The Vatican has purchased the abbey
from the Vasquez family

1352
01:35:42,299 --> 01:35:44,301
and reconsecrated the soil.

1353
01:35:44,385 --> 01:35:47,638
The family has safely relocated
back to the U.S.,

1354
01:35:47,721 --> 01:35:49,848
where the boy made a full recovery.

1355
01:35:54,061 --> 01:35:58,482
The friar's diary is proving very useful,
despite his abhorrence.

1356
01:35:58,565 --> 01:36:02,903
Asmodeus has been defeated,
but there are many more to be found.

1357
01:36:02,987 --> 01:36:08,534
Soon we will know
all of the other 199 sites on earth

1358
01:36:08,617 --> 01:36:10,577
where God is not welcome.

1359
01:36:11,245 --> 01:36:14,331
Gabriele, will you take on this task?

1360
01:36:14,415 --> 01:36:16,709
[pensive music playing]

1361
01:36:16,792 --> 01:36:21,088
This would be more
than a lifetime's work for one priest.

1362
01:36:22,339 --> 01:36:23,674
But two priests...

1363
01:36:25,551 --> 01:36:28,595
What do you think, Tomás?
Can you see this now as a calling?

1364
01:36:29,221 --> 01:36:33,225
And that we must serve God
the way he wants us to serve him?

1365
01:36:35,894 --> 01:36:37,312
Let's go to work.

1366
01:36:40,149 --> 01:36:41,900
Let's go to hell.

1367
01:36:41,984 --> 01:36:45,237
[music turns dramatic]

1368
01:37:08,510 --> 01:37:11,513
[haunting music playing]

1369
01:37:40,584 --> 01:37:42,920
[music intensifies]

1370
01:38:25,587 --> 01:38:28,590
[dramatic music playing]

